Description: Fragment of oval handle at neck join of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine red-brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '45' Name Klenostratos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR 082.31.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (115)
